nytimes_articles.abstract:
The state of Palestine declares its adherence to U.N. principles and goals, and to the principles of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. -- Palestinian Charter of Independence, November 1988. 

     The Palestinian leadership has expressed its commitment to international standards of justice many times over the years. With the establishment of the Palestinian autonomy in Gaza and Jericho last year, however, these ideals have evaporated, leaving nothing but rhetoric. With the elections tomorrow in the West Bank and Gaza, the authority will officially cease to exist, succeeded by an elected president and an 88-member elected legislative council. But will the  Palestinians finally have a democratic government?

nytimes_articles.abstract:
The set for the second scene of Rossini's "Barbiere di Siviglia" snagged and  collapsed on the Metropolitan Opera's revolving turntable near the end of the opening scene on Wednesday evening. No one was hurt, and after a 20-minute delay, the performance proceeded without further incident. 

     When Ruth Ann Swenson, a member of the performance's mostly new cast, made her belated entrance as Rosina, she good-naturedly surveyed the set and crossed  herself, to the audience's relieved amusement. Ms. Swenson sang with a minimum of cuteness, and made a reasonably pleasing sound when she did not force or reach too high.

wiki_events.headline: The barge North Cape oil spill occurs as an engine fire forces the tugboat Scandia ashore on Moonstone Beach in South Kingstown, Rhode Island.

pages.title: North Cape oil spill
pages.description: 1996 oil spill in the United States
pages.abstract: The North Cape oil spill took place on January 19, 1996, when the tank barge North Cape and the tug Scandia grounded on Moonstone Beach in South Kingstown, Rhode Island, after the tug caught fire in its engine room during a winter storm. An estimated 828,000 US gallons (3,130 m3) of home heating oil was spilled. Oil spread throughout a large area of Block Island Sound, including Trustom Pond National Wildlife Refuge, resulting in the closure of a 250-square-mile (650 km2) area of the sound for fishing.

pages.title: South Kingstown, Rhode Island
pages.description: Town in Rhode Island, United States
pages.abstract: South Kingstown is a town in, and the county seat of, Washington County, Rhode Island, United States. The population was 31,931 at the 2020 census. South Kingstown is the second largest town in Rhode Island by total geographic area, behind New Shoreham, and the third largest town in Rhode Island by geographic land area, behind Exeter and Coventry.
